cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the security of a chaotic image cipher and proposes a chosen-plaintext attack, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves the analysis of the data complexity of the proposed attack, which can be considered as an information-theoretic problem. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the design and analysis of a digital image cryptosystem, which can be considered as a system and control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the encryption of digital images, which falls under the scope of multimedia. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper involves the analysis of an image encryption scheme, which can be considered as a computer vision and pattern recognition problem.
